    "narrative_summary": "The BRCA1 missense variant p.Arg1751Pro (R1751P) is recorded in the Breast Cancer Information Core as a known BRCA1 alteration, alongside other changes at the same residue such as R1751Q [PMC2894074]. No specific clinical case reports, segregation data, or formal classification of pathogenicity are provided in the extracted source. The article in which the variant is mentioned focuses on arginine methylation of BRCA1 and does not present functional assays, population frequency data, or computational predictions for R1751P, leaving the biological impact of this substitution uncharacterized. Consequently, the current evidence is insufficient to assign a definitive pathogenic or benign status to BRCA1 R1751P; it remains a variant of uncertain significance pending further clinical or functional investigation.",
